Kursi is an independently designed social-deduction bluffing game
inspired by the social-deduction format popularised by:

  Coup
  Designed by Rikki Tahta
  Published by Indie Boards and Cards (© 2012 Indie Boards and Cards)
  https://www.indieboardsandcards.com

Kursi is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or a product of Indie Boards
and Cards. The game mechanics of bluffing, role-claiming, challenging,
and last-player-standing elimination are general gameplay concepts common
across the social-deduction genre and are not subject to copyright.

Kursi's theme (India corporate-political-underworld satire), all original
text, character names, visual identity, and source code are wholly original
creative works by Siddharth Pandalai.

